where $I$ is the current provided by the user to bias the $Q_{1}-Q_{2}$ pair. The plot of $i_{0}$ versus the difference $v_{P}-v_{N}$ forms the familiar $s$-shaped curve seen in Fig. 4.44. This curve is nonlinear, but if we limit the input voltage to the range $\left|v_{P}-v_{N}\right| \ll 4 V_{T}$ (approximately 100 mV), the small-signal approximation allows us to retain only the first term of the series expansion $\tanh x=x-x^{3}/3+\cdots$ and express

