$$

Using the identity $\ln \left[(1 + x) / (1 - x)\right] = 2 \tan^{-1} x$, which holds for $|x| < 1$, we get:

$$
\begin{equation*}
v_{X} = 2 V_{T} \tan^{-1} \frac{v_{X1} - v_{X2}}{R_{X} I_{X}} \tag{5.77}
\end{equation*}
$$

